    1<sup>st</sup> International  & 4<sup>th</sup> National Conference on Accounting and Fraud Auditing
  </h1>
  <h1 class="fs-3 text-center fw-bold text-black">01-02 February 2023</h1>
  <p class="text-justify fs-6 text-black">
    The National Conference on Accounting & Fraud Auditing (NCAFA) is a national-level conference in the field of accounting and auditing which has a series of Call for Papers and Seminar activities. The purpose of this event is to support the Tri Dharma of higher education, especially in the field of research where NCAFA is a forum for academics, practitioners and students throughout Indonesia to present the best research results in the field of accounting. NCAFA has also become a routine agenda for the Accounting Study Program, Trilogy University since 2019. This conference is a form of contribution from the Accounting Study Program, Trilogy University to the development of accounting science in Indonesia. NCAFA is the result of a collaborative initiative between Trilogy University and the Association of Certified Fraud Examiners (ACFE) Indonesia Chapter and the Association of Public Sector Accounting Educators (APSAE). In its journey the implementation of NCAFA then developed with the cooperation of NCAFA with several SINTA Accredited Journals, the Alliance of Indonesian Integrity Journal Management (ALJEBI), as well as Indonesian State and Private Universities. Along with these developments, the enthusiasm of the participants from year to year has also increased.
  </p>
  <p class="text-justify fs-6 text-black">
    2023 is the fourth year of holding the NCAFA and will be held in a hybrid manner; offline at Trilogy University Auditorium, Jakarta and online through Zoom Cloud Meetings. The 4th NCAFA activity will have an important influence on Trilogy University in establishing scientific communication with academics, business practitioners and public sector actors because the results of the accounting research presented cover various studies, including Financial Accounting and Capital Markets (AKPM), Management Accounting and Behavior (AKMK), Information Systems, Auditing, and Professional Ethics (SIAEP), Taxation (PPJK), Sharia Accounting (AKSR), Governance and Sustainability Accounting (TKSA), Fraud and Forensic Accounting (FFA), Public Sector Accounting ( ASP), and Accounting Education (PAk).
  </p>
  <p class="text-justify fs-6 text-black">
    The results of this conference are expected to provide alternative solutions that bridge views based on theory and research results in the scientific world with practical realities in both the business sector and the public sector. This conference is also expected to contribute constructive ideas as recommendations for government policies, especially the role of accountants in preventing fraud, tax regulations, and policies in the capital market and money market sectors.
  </p>
